        <abstract>
            <title>EPUB Publications 3.1</title>
            <para>EPUB is an interchange and delivery format for digital publications based on XML and Web Standards.</para>
        </abstract>
    </info>

    <chapter xml:id="sec-intro">
        <title>Introduction</title>

        <para>This specification, EPUB 3.1, defines a distribution and interchange format standard for digital publications
            and documents. EPUB® defines a means of representing, packaging and encoding structured and semantically enhanced
            Web content — including HTML5, CSS, SVG and other resources — for distribution in a single-file format.</para>

        <para>EPUB has been widely adopted as the format for digital books (eBooks), and these specifications significantly
            increase the format's capabilities in order to better support a wider range of publication requirements,
            including complex layouts, rich media and interactivity, and global typography features. The expectation is that
            EPUB 3 will be utilized for a broad range of content, including books, magazines and educational, professional
            and scientific publications.</para>

    </chapter>

    <chapter xml:id="sec-specs">
        <title>EPUB Specifications</title>

        <section xml:id="sec-spec-overview" conformance="informative">
            <title>Overview</title>
            <para>This specification provides only a basic listing of the core and satellite EPUB 3 specifications. A more
                comprehensive introduction to features and functionality that EPUB 3 provides is included in the informative
                    <xref linkend="refEPUB3Overview"/>.</para>

            <para>A list of changes from EPUB 3.0.1 is also provided in the informative <xref linkend="refEPUB3Changes"
                />.</para>
        </section>

        <section xml:id="sec-specs-core">
            <title>Core</title>

            <para>The EPUB 3.1 core is defined as the set of specifications that contain the essential information that <link
                    linkend="gloss-author">Authors</link> need to create and package <link linkend="gloss-epub-publication"
                    >EPUB Publications</link> and that <link linkend="gloss-epub-reading-system">Reading System</link>
                developers require to ingest them.</para>

            <para>The core is composed of the following specifications:</para>

            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>EPUB Publications 3.1 <xref linkend="refPublications3"/>, which defines the semantics and
                        overarching conformance requirements for EPUB Publications, including the requirements for each
                            <olink targetdoc="spec" targetptr="gloss-rendition" type="epub-spec"/> of the content and the
                        profiles of XHTML, SVG and CSS.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>EPUB Media Overlays 3.1 <xref linkend="refOverlays3"/>, which defines a format and a processing
                        model for synchronization of text and audio.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>EPUB Open Container Format (OCF) 3.1 <xref linkend="refOCF3"/>, which defines a file format and
                        processing model for encapsulating a set of related resources into a single-file (ZIP) <xref
                            linkend="gloss-container"/>.</para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </section>

        <section xml:id="sec-specs-modules">
            <title>Modules</title>

            <para>The following specifications are considered modular extensions of the EPUB 3.1 core as they layer
                additional functionality on EPUB Publications:</para>

            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>EPUB Canonical Fragment Identifiers (epubcfi) <xref linkend="refEPUBCFI"/>, which defines a
                        standardized method for referencing arbitrary content within an EPUB Publication through the use of
                        fragment identifiers.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Alternate Style Tags <xref linkend="refAlternateStyleTags"/>, which defines a pattern for tagging
                        alternate style sheets using microformats.</para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </section>
    </chapter>

    <chapter xml:id="sec-terminology">
        <title>Terminology</title>

        <glosslist xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
            xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" version="5.1" xmlns:epub="http://www.idpf.org/2011/epub">

            <glossentry xml:id="gloss-author" xreflabel="Author">
                <glossterm>Author</glossterm>
                <glossdef>
                    <para>The person(s) or organization responsible for the creation of an <xref
                            linkend="gloss-epub-publication"/>, which is not necessarily the creator of the content and
                        resources it contains. </para>
                </glossdef>
            </glossentry>

            <glossentry xml:id="gloss-content-provider" xreflabel="Content Provider">
                <glossterm>Content Provider</glossterm>
                <glossdef>
                    <para>A publisher, author, individual, or other information source that provides <xref
                            linkend="gloss-epub-publication"/>s to distribution or sales channels or directly to one or more
                            <xref linkend="gloss-epub-reading-system"/>s
                        <!-- using OCF as described in this
                specification-->.</para>
                </glossdef>
            </glossentry>

            <glossentry xml:id="gloss-core-media-type" xreflabel="Core Media Type">
                <glossterm>Core Media Type</glossterm>
                <glossdef>
                    <para>A set of <xref linkend="gloss-publication-resource-cmt-or-foreign"/> types for which no fallback is
                        required. Refer to <olink targetdoc="publications" targetptr="sec-publication-resources"
                            type="epub-spec"/> for more information. </para>
                </glossdef>
            </glossentry>

            <glossentry xml:id="gloss-publication-resource-cmt" xreflabel="Core Media Type Resource">
                <glossterm>Core Media Type Resource</glossterm>
                <glossdef>
                    <para>A <xref linkend="gloss-publication-resource-cmt-or-foreign"/> that is a <xref
                            linkend="gloss-core-media-type"/> and may therefore be included in the <xref
                            linkend="gloss-epub-publication"/> without the provision of <olink targetdoc="publications"
                            targetptr="sec-fallback-processing-flow" type="epub-spec">fallbacks</olink>
                        <olink targetdoc="publications" targetptr="sec-fallback-processing-flow" type="epub-spec"
                            >fallbacks</olink>.</para>
                </glossdef>
            </glossentry>

            <glossentry xml:id="gloss-viewport-css" xreflabel="CSS Viewport">
                <glossterm>CSS Viewport</glossterm>
                <glossdef>
                    <para>A <xref linkend="gloss-viewport"/> capable of displaying CSS-styled content.</para>
                </glossdef>
            </glossentry>

            <glossentry xml:id="gloss-rendition-default" xreflabel="Default Rendition">
                <glossterm>Default Rendition</glossterm>
                <glossdef>
                    <para>The <xref linkend="gloss-rendition"/> listed in the first <markup>rootfile</markup> element in the
                            <olink targetdoc="ocf" targetptr="sec-container-metainf-container.xml" type="epub-spec"
                            >container.xml</olink> file.</para>
                </glossdef>
            </glossentry>

